'''Mory Diaw''' (born 22 June 1993) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{French football updater|Le Havre}} club [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]].

==Club career==
Diaw began his career in the youth teams of [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] (PSG). He made one senior appearance, playing 17 minutes in a friendly against [[TSV Hartberg]] on 8 July 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.psg.fr/en/Actus/003001/Article/67441/Une-victoire-pour-demarrer |title=Paris Start with a Win |date=8 July 2014 |access-date=12 March 2016 |work=Paris Saint Germain}}</ref> After being released by PSG in 2015, Diaw signed for Portuguese [[LigaPro|Segunda Liga]] outfit [[C.D. Mafra|Mafra]] on 29 July 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/segunda_liga/artigo/2015/07/29/mafra-contrata-mory-diaw |title=Mafra contrata Mory Diaw |date=29 July 2015 |access-date=12 March 2016 |work=Sapo de Sporto |language=Portuguese}}</ref>

In April 2017, Diaw went on trial with [[EFL Championship]] side [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hitc.com/en-gb/2017/04/10/five-facts-on-leeds-trialist-mory-diaw-including-twitter-storm-c/ |title=Five facts on Leeds trialist Mory Diaw: including Twitter storm, comments on ex-Whites defender |date=10 April 2017 |access-date=16 May 2017 |work=HITC}}</ref> He joined Bulgarian side Lokomotiv Plovdiv in July 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lokomotivpd.com/dvama-novi-se-prisaediniha-kam-lokomotiv/ |title=Двама нови се присъединиха към Локомотив |date=5 July 2017 |access-date=8 July 2017 |work=PFC Lokomotiv Plovdiv |language=Bulgarian}}</ref> Following a short and successful trial period, on 8 July 2017 he signed a 2-year contract.<ref>{{cite web | title = Локомотив подписа договор с вратаря Мори Диау | url = https://lokomotivpd.com/lokomotiv-podpisa-dogovor-s-vratarya-mori-diau/ | publisher = lokomotivpd.com | date = 8 July 2017 | language = Bulgarian}}</ref>

In 2019, Diaw joined FC United Zürich in Switzerland.<ref>[https://www.lestitisdupsg.fr/anciens-mory-diaw-rebondit-au-fc-united-zurich-d4sui/ &#91;ANCIENS&#93; MORY DIAW REBONDIT AU FC UNITED ZURICH (D4/SUI)], lestitisdupsg.fr, 24 March 2019</ref> In June 2019, he signed for second-tier Swiss club [[FC Lausanne-Sport|Lausanne-Sport]], where he replaced the injured second goalkeeper Dany Da Silva.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.24heures.ch/sports/ls/mory-diaw-signe-pour-six-mois-au-ls/story/13503728|author=Sport-Center|title=Mory Diaw signe pour six mois au LS|work=[[24 heures (Switzerland)|24 heures]]|access-date=26 June 2019|date=26 June 2019}}.</ref>

Diaw made his return to France on 14 June 2022, signing for [[Ligue 1]] side [[Clermont Foot|Clermont]] on a two-year contract with an option for a further year.<ref>{{Cite web |date=15 June 2022 |title=Mory Diaw en renfort |trans-title=Mory Diaw as reinforcement |url=https://www.clermontfoot.com/mory-diaw-en-renfort/ |access-date=15 June 2022 |publisher=[[Clermont Foot]] |language=fr}}</ref>

On 8 October 2023, in a Ligue 1 match at [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]], Diaw was hit by a firework thrown from the crowd, leading to the abandonment of the match.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Mory-diaw-apte-a-rejoindre-la-selection-senegalaise-apres-l-incident-du-petard-a-montpellier/1424394|title=Mory Diaw apte à rejoindre la sélection sénégalaise après l'incident du pétard à Montpellier|language=French|date=9 October 2023|access-date=29 December 2023|website=L'Équipe}}</ref>

On 3 February 2025, Diaw moved on loan to [[Rodez AF|Rodez]] in [[Ligue 2]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Rodez AF|url=https://rodezaveyronfootball.com/2025/02/mercato-mory-diaw-au-raf/|title=Mercato : Mory Diaw au RAF !|trans-title=Transfer window: Mory Diaw at RAF!|date=3 February 2025|access-date=5 February 2025|language=fr}}</ref>

On 12 July 2025, Diaw signed a two-season contract with [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Le Havre AC|url=https://www.hac-foot.com/actualite/mory-diaw-rejoint-le-hac.html|title=Mory Diaw rejoint le HAC !|trans-title=Mory Diaw joins HAC!|date=12 July 2025|access-date=1 August 2025|language=fr}}</ref>

==International career==
Diaw made his international debut for [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]] in a 4–2 friendly win over [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] on 21 June 2023.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clermontfoot.com/les-resultats-de-nos-internationaux-3/|title=LES RÉSULTATS DE NOS INTERNATIONAUX|language=French|date=21 June 2023|access-date=29 December 2023|website=Clermont Foot 63}}</ref>

In December 2023, he was named in Senegal's squad for the postponed [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] held in the [[Ivory Coast]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/africa/67840713|title=Afcon 2023: Senegal and Sadio Mane set for defence of title|date=29 December 2023|access-date=29 December 2023|work=BBC Sport Africa}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Born in France, Diaw is of Senegalese descent.<ref>{{cite news |last=Cissé |first=Bacary |date=18 June 2014 |title=ECHO DE LA TANIERE - MORY DIAW, GARDIEN DE BUT PARIS SG - "Intégrer la Tanière n'est plus un rêve, mais un objectif" |language=French |publisher=seneplus.com |url=http://www.seneplus.com/article/echo-de-la-taniere-mory-diaw-gardien-de-paris-sg-%C2%ABint%C3%A9grer-la-tani%C3%A8re-n%E2%80%99est-plus-un-r%C3%AAve |access-date=11 June 2018}}</ref>

During his time at Paris Saint-Germain, Diaw became a trending topic on social media site [[Twitter]] after a string of obscene tweets posted by his account. Tweets included vulgar jokes and even posting the phone number of teammate [[Zlatan Ibrahimović]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rtl.fr/sport/football/mory-diaw-les-tweets-embarrassants-d-un-jeune-joueur-du-psg-7778419714 |title=Mory Diaw : les tweets embarrassants d'un jeune joueur du PSG |date=20 May 2015 |access-date=12 March 2016 |work=RTL |language=French}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sofoot.com/quand-mory-diaw-a-fait-disjoncter-twitter-201486.html |title=Quand Mory Diaw a Fait Disjoncter Twitter |date=20 May 2015 |access-date=12 March 2016 |work=SoFoot |language=French}}</ref> Club officials were quick to address the issue, claiming Diaw's account had been hacked.<ref>{{Twitter|PSG_inside/status/600953694646067200|Paris Saint Germain}}</ref> The tweets have since been deleted.{{Citation needed|date=June 2022}}

